YELP 365 CHALLENGE 2014-(152/365) "King George"  So it was the week of the Second Chance Prom at the Palms, and my hair was already looking bushwhacked, but I figured I'd wait until Saturday, the day of the prom, and the only day that I'm able to see my barber due to my work schedule.
Fast forward to Thursday, a notice is posted up on Instagram by my barber stating that they will CLOSED Friday and Saturday(Prom Night)  NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!!
NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!!
NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!!
Just my luck, I tried not to panic, and the one time I cut my hair out of desperation, I came out looking like Mr.Clean,(No Lie!
) so I needed to book an appointment and FAST!
My previous review of Fade Kingz Barber Shop wasn't a very good first impression, but looking at the pictures of haircuts done by George convinced me to give it another go.
I booked an appointment with George first thing in the morning on Saturday.
9 am Satuday morning, first one in the door with no wait, I met up with George, told him what I wanted, and he did his magic.
it was clean and spacious inside and the guys were cool and able to carry on conversations, etc.
30 minutes later, I was done, relieved, and happy that George came through, and I have a go-to spot if I ever come across this same situation.
Know before you go:  Haircuts start at $18, Shaves  are $15  Best to make an appointment ahead of time-filled up with walk-ins by the time I was done  They are open later hours than some barbers, but prices may be higher  during the later hours  Located in the NW, same place as Comic Oasis, Marshalls, etc.
If you live on this side of town, definitely check out Fade Kingz!
ALOHA!!!
